tComponentid.name: tComponentid
tComponentid.description: This group defines the attributes common to all components. This group is required.

a1Installation.name: a1Installation
a1Installation.description: The installation date and time of this component. The Service Layer assigns this value, the manufacturer should leave it blank.

a1Verify.name: a1Verify
a1Verify.description: A code that provides a level of verification that the component is still installed and working.

tSubcomponentSoftware.name: tSubcomponentSoftware
tSubcomponentSoftware.description: This group describes the software resources that are used by a component or subcomponent.

a2SoftwareIndex.name: a2SoftwareIndex
a2SoftwareIndex.description: An index into the SubComponent Software table

a2Type.name: a2Type
a2Type.description: The type of software resource described by this row. For example this value would be 'Device Driver', 'INF File', 'Boot ROM', and etc.

a2Vendor.name: a2Vendor
a2Vendor.description: The name of the vendor who supplied this piece of software.

a2Version.name: a2Version
a2Version.description: The revision level of this piece of software. For example the Version Major, Version Minor, Revision, and Build numbers.

a2Description.name: a2Description
a2Description.description: An additional description of this piece of software

a2IdentificationCode.name: a2IdentificationCode
a2IdentificationCode.description: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU) or Part Number for this piece of software.

a2LanguageEdition.name: a2LanguageEdition
a2LanguageEdition.description: Identifies the language edition of this piece of software.

a2InterfaceDescription.name: a2InterfaceDescription
a2InterfaceDescription.description: This is the specification or operating system to which this piece of software conforms. (e.g. 'Microsoft NT', 'NetWare', etc.)

a2InterfaceVersion.name: a2InterfaceVersion
a2InterfaceVersion.description: The specification or operating system version to which this piece of software conforms. (e.g. '4.0 or higher', '3.xx', etc.)

a3WorldwideIdentifierIndex.name: a3WorldwideIdentifierIndex
a3WorldwideIdentifierIndex.description: An index into the Worldwide Identifier table.

a3WorldwideIdentifierType.name: a3WorldwideIdentifierType
a3WorldwideIdentifierType.description: The type of identifier displayed by the Worldwide Identifier attribute.

a3WorldwideIdentifier.name: a3WorldwideIdentifier
a3WorldwideIdentifier.description: The Worldwide identifier for this device.

tFieldReplaceableUnit.name: tFieldReplaceableUnit
tFieldReplaceableUnit.description: A Field Replaceable Unit (FRU), is defined as a hardware component which is designed to be separately removable for replacement or repair. For the purposes of this definition, a motherboard and a fixed hard disk are FRUs, whereas a fixed hard disk platter or a chip fixed in place on the motherboard are not FRUs since they are not designed to be separately removable. Each instance within the FRU table should contain the device group and instance data for the associated hardware component.

a4FruIndex.name: a4FruIndex
a4FruIndex.description: The index into the Field Replaceable Unit table.

a4DeviceGroupIndex.name: a4DeviceGroupIndex
a4DeviceGroupIndex.description: The group ID of the group referencing this Field Replaceable Unit instance.

a4Description.name: a4Description
a4Description.description: A clear description of this Field Replaceable Unit.

a4Manufacturer.name: a4Manufacturer
a4Manufacturer.description: The name of the company manufacturing or providing this Field Replaceable Unit.

a4Model.name: a4Model
a4Model.description: The manufacturer's model number for this Field Replaceable Unit.

a4PartNumber.name: a4PartNumber
a4PartNumber.description: A part number by which a replacement part can be ordered for this Field Replaceable Unit.

a4FruSerialNumber.name: a4FruSerialNumber
a4FruSerialNumber.description: The manufacturer's serial number for this Field Replaceable Unit.

a4RevisionLevel.name: a4RevisionLevel
a4RevisionLevel.description: The revision level of this Field Replaceable Unit.

a4WarrantyStartDate.name: a4WarrantyStartDate
a4WarrantyStartDate.description: The start date of the service warranty for this Field Replaceabl Unit.

a4WarrantyDuration.name: a4WarrantyDuration
a4WarrantyDuration.description: The total duration of this Field Replaceable Unit warranty in months.

a4SupportPhoneNumber.name: a4SupportPhoneNumber
a4SupportPhoneNumber.description: The phone number(s) for support for this Field Replaceable Unit.

a4FruInternetUniformResourceLocator.name: a4FruInternetUniformResourceLocator
a4FruInternetUniformResourceLocator.description: The Internet Uniform Resource Locator string that can be used through a World Wide Web browser to obtain further information about this FRU

tStorageDevices.name: tStorageDevices
tStorageDevices.description: This group defines the mass storage devices in this system.

a5StorageDeviceIndex.name: a5StorageDeviceIndex
a5StorageDeviceIndex.description: An index into the storage device table.

a5Type.name: a5Type
a5Type.description: The type of this mass storage device. If 'Other' is used, then the Type Description attribute shall be used.

a5TypeDescription.name: a5TypeDescription
a5TypeDescription.description: A longer description of the storage device. For example: 3.5 inch flexible diskette drive using diskettes with a maximum capacity of 1.44MB. If 'Other' was specified above, then this field shall be used. Otherwise, the contents of this optional field shall not contradict the Storage Device Type specified above.

a5Sub_identifier.name: a5Sub_identifier
a5Sub_identifier.description: The sub-identifier for this storage device (e.g., the device's SCSI logical unit number).

a5MediaDataBlockSize.name: a5MediaDataBlockSize
a5MediaDataBlockSize.description: The size in bytes of the data blocks used on the storage media. If the media block size is unknown or not consistent across the media, then this value shall be zero.

a5FormattedMediaCapacity.name: a5FormattedMediaCapacity
a5FormattedMediaCapacity.description: The total size in bytes of this storage media after it has been formatted.

a5RemovableDevice.name: a5RemovableDevice
a5RemovableDevice.description: If true, then this storage device is removable (e.g.: PCMCIA device).

a5DeviceLoaded.name: a5DeviceLoaded
a5DeviceLoaded.description: If true, then the storage device is loaded. If the device is not removable, then this value shall be 'TRUE'.

a5RemovableMedia.name: a5RemovableMedia
a5RemovableMedia.description: If true, then the media in this storage device is removable.

a5MediaLoaded.name: a5MediaLoaded
a5MediaLoaded.description: If true, the media in this storage device is loaded. If the media is not removable, then this value shall be 'TRUE'

a5Compression.name: a5Compression
a5Compression.description: If true, the storage device supports compression.

a5Encryption.name: a5Encryption
a5Encryption.description: If true, the storage device supports encryption.

a6StorageDevicesEventType.name: a6StorageDevicesEventType
a6StorageDevicesEventType.description: The type of Storage Devices event that has occurred.

a6EventIsStateBased.name: a6EventIsStateBased
a6EventIsStateBased.description: The value of this attribute determined whether the Event being reported is a state-based Event or not. If the value of this attribute is TRUE then the Event is state-based. Else the Event is not state-based

a6EventStateKey.name: a6EventStateKey
a6EventStateKey.description: This attribute holds the key identifying a row of the Event State group within the Component in which the event generator group is located. The Current State attribute within the row contains the current state of this state-based event. The current state can be one of the four severities: OK, Non-Critical, Critical, and Non-Recoverable.

a6EventSystem.name: a6EventSystem
a6EventSystem.description: The major functional aspect of the product causing the fault.

a6EventSubsystem.name: a6EventSubsystem
a6EventSubsystem.description: The minor functional aspect of the product causing the fault.

tStorageController.name: tStorageController
tStorageController.description: This group defines the storage controller in this system.

a7ControllerIndex.name: a7ControllerIndex
a7ControllerIndex.description: An index into the Storage Controller table.

a7Identification.name: a7Identification
a7Identification.description: e.g. Name, brand and hardware revision level of the storage controller.

a7ProtectionManagement.name: a7ProtectionManagement
a7ProtectionManagement.description: Indicates whether or not the controller provides redundancy or protection against device failures.

a7BusMaster.name: a7BusMaster
a7BusMaster.description: If true, then this storage controller is the bus master.

a7SecondsSinceLastPower_up.name: a7SecondsSinceLastPower_up
a7SecondsSinceLastPower_up.description: The number of seconds that have passed since this controller was last powered on.

a8StorageControllerEventType.name: a8StorageControllerEventType
a8StorageControllerEventType.description: The type of Storage Controller event that has occurred.

a8EventIsStateBased.name: a8EventIsStateBased
a8EventIsStateBased.description: The value of this attribute determined whether the Event being reported is a state-based Event or not. If the value of this attribute is TRUE then the Event is state-based. Else the Event is not state-based

a8EventStateKey.name: a8EventStateKey
a8EventStateKey.description: This attribute holds the key identifying a row of the Event State group within the Component in which the event generator group is located. The Current State attribute within the row contains the current state of this state-based event. The current state can be one of the four severities: OK, Non-Critical, Critical, and Non-Recoverable.

a8EventSystem.name: a8EventSystem
a8EventSystem.description: The major functional aspect of the product causing the fault.

a8EventSubsystem.name: a8EventSubsystem
a8EventSubsystem.description: The minor functional aspect of the product causing the fault.

tBusPort.name: tBusPort
tBusPort.description: This global table has one entry for each of the Bus Ports in this Component.

a9BusPortIndex.name: a9BusPortIndex
a9BusPortIndex.description: An index into the Bus Port table.

a9Protocol.name: a9Protocol
a9Protocol.description: The protocol describing the electrical characteristic of the Bus Port. If 'Other' is used, then the Protocol Description attribute shall be used.

a9ProtocolDescription.name: a9ProtocolDescription
a9ProtocolDescription.description: Additional description of the protocol described above. If 'Other' was specified above, then this field shall be used. Otherwise, the contents of this optional field shall not contradict the Protocol specified above.

a9SignalCharacteristics.name: a9SignalCharacteristics
a9SignalCharacteristics.description: The signal characteristics of the Bus Port being described.

a9AddressDescriptor.name: a9AddressDescriptor
a9AddressDescriptor.description: The address descriptor of this bus port. For example, the SCSI address of this port.

a9Isochronous.name: a9Isochronous
a9Isochronous.description: Indicates whether or not this bus port supports isochronous transfers.

a9MaximumWidth.name: a9MaximumWidth
a9MaximumWidth.description: The maximum width, in bits, of this Bus Port's data path. A value of 1 should be used for serial.

a9MaximumTransferRate.name: a9MaximumTransferRate
a9MaximumTransferRate.description: The theoretical maximum transfer rate, in millions of bytes per second, that this Bus Port is capable of achieving under ideal conditions. A value of zero should be used if the transfer rate is less than 1 million bytes per second. A value of 0x80000000 should be used if the transfer rate is unknown.

a9MaximumNumberOfAttachments.name: a9MaximumNumberOfAttachments
a9MaximumNumberOfAttachments.description: The maximum number of directly addressable entities supported by this bus port's protocol. A value of zero should be used if the number of attachments is unknown.

a9ConnectorType.name: a9ConnectorType
a9ConnectorType.description: Describes how options (cards, devices, etc.) physically connect to this bus port. If 'Other' is used, then the Connector Type Description attribute shall be used.

a9ConnectorTypeDescription.name: a9ConnectorTypeDescription
a9ConnectorTypeDescription.description: An additional text description of the type of connector describe above. If 'Other' was specified above, then this field shall be used. Otherwis , the contents of this optional field shall not contradict the connector specified above.

a9ConnectorGender.name: a9ConnectorGender
a9ConnectorGender.description: Indicates the gender of the connector described above.

tFibreChannelBusPortExtensions.name: tFibreChannelBusPortExtensions
tFibreChannelBusPortExtensions.description: This group extents the Bus Port group with Fibre Channel specific attributes.

a10BusPortIndex.name: a10BusPortIndex
a10BusPortIndex.description: The index into the Bus Port Table that this Fibre Channel group is extending.

a10EndToEndCredit.name: a10EndToEndCredit
a10EndToEndCredit.description: The number of allowable outstanding acknowledgments for a sequence.

a10BufferToBufferCredit.name: a10BufferToBufferCredit
a10BufferToBufferCredit.description: The number of frames which can be handled by the node before a wait for the buffer ready is required, and prior to subsequent frame transmiss ons.

a10LinkType.name: a10LinkType
a10LinkType.description: Reports whether copper or fibre media is used.

a10FlowControlClassType.name: a10FlowControlClassType
a10FlowControlClassType.description: Identifies the Flow Control Class Type.

a10FlowControlAcknowledgmentType.name: a10FlowControlAcknowledgmentType
a10FlowControlAcknowledgmentType.description: Identifies the Flow Control Acknowledgment Type.

a10FabricTopology.name: a10FabricTopology
a10FabricTopology.description: If true, a fabric topology exists within the fibre channel bus port.

tMassStorageAssociation.name: tMassStorageAssociation
tMassStorageAssociation.description: Mass storage associations define the relationships between the various components of the Storage Subsystem.

a11AssociationIndex.name: a11AssociationIndex
a11AssociationIndex.description: An index into the Association table.

a11Type.name: a11Type
a11Type.description: This field specifies the type of the association.

a12MassStorageAssociationEventType.name: a12MassStorageAssociationEventType
a12MassStorageAssociationEventType.description: The type of Mass storage association where a change has occurred

a12EventIsStateBased.name: a12EventIsStateBased
a12EventIsStateBased.description: The value of this attribute determined whether the Event being reported is a state-based Event or not. If the value of this attribute is TRUE then the Event is state-based. Else the Event is not state-based

a12EventStateKey.name: a12EventStateKey
a12EventStateKey.description: This attribute holds the key identifying a row of the Event State group within the Component in which the event generator group is located. The Current State attribute within the row contains the current state of this state-based event. The current state can be one of the four severities: OK, Non-Critical, Critical, and Non-Recoverable.

a12AssociatedGroup.name: a12AssociatedGroup
a12AssociatedGroup.description: The class name of the group that is associated with the events defined in this EventGeneration group.

a12EventSystem.name: a12EventSystem
a12EventSystem.description: The mass storage association object type which is causing a change.

a12EventSubsystem.name: a12EventSubsystem
a12EventSubsystem.description: The minor functional aspect of the product causing the fault.

a13BusPortAssociationIndex.name: a13BusPortAssociationIndex
a13BusPortAssociationIndex.description: An index into the Bus Port Association table. This index is the same as the index in the Association group that defines the bus port association.

a13NegotiatedSpeed.name: a13NegotiatedSpeed
a13NegotiatedSpeed.description: The maximum burst transfer rate, in millions of bytes, which was negotiated between the two associated bus ports.

a13NegotiatedWidth.name: a13NegotiatedWidth
a13NegotiatedWidth.description: The width, in bits, of the bus ports data path which was negotiated between the two associated bus ports.

tOperationalState.name: tOperationalState
tOperationalState.description: This group provides the operational state, usage, and availabili y status, and administrative state indicators for specific Device Group instance .

a14OperationalStateInstanceIndex.name: a14OperationalStateInstanceIndex
a14OperationalStateInstanceIndex.description: The Index into the Operational State table.

a14DeviceGroupIndex.name: a14DeviceGroupIndex
a14DeviceGroupIndex.description: The group ID of the group referencing this instance.

a14OperationalStatus.name: a14OperationalStatus
a14OperationalStatus.description: The operational status of the Device Group instance.

a14UsageState.name: a14UsageState
a14UsageState.description: The usage state of the Device Group instance.

a14AvailabilityStatus.name: a14AvailabilityStatus
a14AvailabilityStatus.description: The availability status of the Device Group instance.

a14AdministrativeState.name: a14AdministrativeState
a14AdministrativeState.description: The administrative state of the Device Group instance.

a14FatalErrorCount.name: a14FatalErrorCount
a14FatalErrorCount.description: The accumulated Fatal or Non-recoverable error count for this Device Group instance.

a14MajorErrorCount.name: a14MajorErrorCount
a14MajorErrorCount.description: The accumulated Major or Critical error count for this Device Group instance.

a14WarningErrorCount.name: a14WarningErrorCount
a14WarningErrorCount.description: The accumulated Warning or Non-Critical error count for this Device Group instance.

a14CurrentErrorStatus.name: a14CurrentErrorStatus
a14CurrentErrorStatus.description: This attribute presents the current error status for this Device Group instance. The most critical error status in effect should be presented. I.e. if a part of the Device Group instance is 'Critical', while other status is 'Non-critical' then the status 'Critical' should be reported.

a14DevicePredictedFailureStatus.name: a14DevicePredictedFailureStatus
a14DevicePredictedFailureStatus.description: Enumeration describing the current Device Predicted Failure Status (e.g.: the S.M.A.R.T. status of the device).

tSymbiosEventPolling.name: tSymbiosEventPolling
tSymbiosEventPolling.description: This group is the Symbios Vendor unique group for dealing with Event Polling.

a15SmartEventPolling.name: a15SmartEventPolling
a15SmartEventPolling.description: A flag indicating whether or not the CI will poll for SMART events.

a15ScanEventPolling.name: a15ScanEventPolling
a15ScanEventPolling.description: A flag indicating whether or not the CI will scan for a change in Devices and Controllers.

a15Saf_teEventPolling.name: a15Saf_teEventPolling
a15Saf_teEventPolling.description: A flag indicating whether or not the CI will poll for SAF-TE events.

a15EventPollingPeriod.name: a15EventPollingPeriod
a15EventPollingPeriod.description: The event poll period in number of minutes.

tSymbiosSmartDevice.name: tSymbiosSmartDevice
tSymbiosSmartDevice.description: This group is a Symbios Vendor unique group for dealing with Smart Storage Devices.

a16SymSmartDeviceIndex.name: a16SymSmartDeviceIndex
a16SymSmartDeviceIndex.description: An index into the Symbios Vendor Unique Device info table. This index corresponds to the Storage Device index.

a16SmartReportingCapability.name: a16SmartReportingCapability
a16SmartReportingCapability.description: A flag indicating the state of a Devices's SMART reporting capability.

tSaf_teProcessor.name: tSaf_teProcessor
tSaf_teProcessor.description: This group defines a SAF-TE Processor

a17Saf_teProcessorIndex.name: a17Saf_teProcessorIndex
a17Saf_teProcessorIndex.description: An index into the SAF-TE processor table.

a17StorageControllerIndex.name: a17StorageControllerIndex
a17StorageControllerIndex.description: An index into the Storage Controller table.

a17VendorId.name: a17VendorId
a17VendorId.description: The vendor ID that is returned in the Inquiry command

a17ProductId.name: a17ProductId
a17ProductId.description: The product ID that is returned in the Inquiry command

a17FirmwareRevisionLevel.name: a17FirmwareRevisionLevel
a17FirmwareRevisionLevel.description: Identifies the current firmware revision of the SAF-TE processor

a17EnclosureUniqueIdentifier.name: a17EnclosureUniqueIdentifier
a17EnclosureUniqueIdentifier.description: This field specifies the unique unit number for the SAF-TE processor.

a17Saf_teSpecificationRevisionLevel.name: a17Saf_teSpecificationRevisionLevel
a17Saf_teSpecificationRevisionLevel.description: Identifies the revision of the SAF-TE interface specification to which this device claims compliance.

a17HasLocks.name: a17HasLocks
a17HasLocks.description: If true, then this SAF-TE processor is contained within an enclosure that has locks.

a17HasSpeakers.name: a17HasSpeakers
a17HasSpeakers.description: If true, then this SAF-TE processor is contained within an enclosure that has speakers.

a17DoorLocked.name: a17DoorLocked
a17DoorLocked.description: If true, then this SAF-TE processor enclosure is locked.

a17SpeakerStatus.name: a17SpeakerStatus
a17SpeakerStatus.description: If true, then this SAF-TE processor enclsoure speakers are turned on. If false, then the speakers are off or not installed.

a17PowerOnMinutes.name: a17PowerOnMinutes
a17PowerOnMinutes.description: Total number of power on minutes.

a17PowerOnCycles.name: a17PowerOnCycles
a17PowerOnCycles.description: Total number of times the SAF-TE enclosure has been power on.

a17TemperatureOutOfRange.name: a17TemperatureOutOfRange
a17TemperatureOutOfRange.description: If true, then the temperature is out of range.

tSaf_teControlledFan.name: tSaf_teControlledFan
tSaf_teControlledFan.description: This group defines status of a fan controlled by a SAF-TE Processor

a18Saf_teControlledFanIndex.name: a18Saf_teControlledFanIndex
a18Saf_teControlledFanIndex.description: An index into the SAF-TE controlled fan table.

a18Saf_teProcessorIndex.name: a18Saf_teProcessorIndex
a18Saf_teProcessorIndex.description: The Index to the SAF-TE proccessor that is controlling this fan.

tSaf_teControlledPowerSupply.name: tSaf_teControlledPowerSupply
tSaf_teControlledPowerSupply.description: This group defines status of a Power Supply controlled by a SAF-TE Processor

a19Saf_teControlledPowerSupplyIndex.name: a19Saf_teControlledPowerSupplyIndex
a19Saf_teControlledPowerSupplyIndex.description: An index into the SAF-TE controlled Power Supply table.

a19Saf_teProcessorIndex.name: a19Saf_teProcessorIndex
a19Saf_teProcessorIndex.description: The Index to the SAF-TE proccessor that is controlling this Power Supply.

tSaf_teControlledSlot.name: tSaf_teControlledSlot
tSaf_teControlledSlot.description: This group defines status of a Slot controlled by a SAF-TE Processor

a20Saf_teControlledSlotIndex.name: a20Saf_teControlledSlotIndex
a20Saf_teControlledSlotIndex.description: An index into the SAF-TE controlled Slot table.

a20Saf_teProcessorIndex.name: a20Saf_teProcessorIndex
a20Saf_teProcessorIndex.description: The Index to the SAF-TE proccessor table that is controlling this Slot.

a20ScsiId.name: a20ScsiId
a20ScsiId.description: The SCSI target/initiator identifier for this slot.

a20NumberOfInsertions.name: a20NumberOfInsertions
a20NumberOfInsertions.description: The total number of device insertions for this slot while the enclosure is powered on.

a20DeviceFault.name: a20DeviceFault
a20DeviceFault.description: If true, the device has exhibited some hardware or data fault.

a20InFailedArray.name: a20InFailedArray
a20InFailedArray.description: If true, the device is in an array and an error has occurred on any member of the array.

a20InCriticalArray.name: a20InCriticalArray
a20InCriticalArray.description: If true, the device is in an array that is non fault-tolerant.

a20ParityCheck.name: a20ParityCheck
a20ParityCheck.description: If true, the device is in an array that is undergoing a parity check operation.

a20PredictedFault.name: a20PredictedFault
a20PredictedFault.description: If true, the device has been tagged by a fault prediction algorithm as being likely to fail in the near future.

tSaf_teControlledTemperatureSensor.name: tSaf_teControlledTemperatureSensor
tSaf_teControlledTemperatureSensor.description: This group defines status of a Temperature sensor controlled by a SAF-TE Processor

a21Saf_teControlledTemperatureSensorInde.name: a21Saf_teControlledTemperatureSensorInde
a21Saf_teControlledTemperatureSensorInde.description: An index into the SAF-TE controlled Temperature sensor table.

a21Saf_teProcessorIndex.name: a21Saf_teProcessorIndex
a21Saf_teProcessorIndex.description: The Index to the SAF-TE proccessor that is controlling this Temperature sensor.

a21Temperature.name: a21Temperature
a21Temperature.description: The current temperature in degrees Fahrenheit.

tNetworkAdapter802PortGroup.name: tNetworkAdapter802PortGroup
tNetworkAdapter802PortGroup.description: Contains objects related to each of the network ports on the network adapter.

a22PortIndex.name: a22PortIndex
a22PortIndex.description: This attribute is the ordinal of the network port within the network adapter, i.e. the 'port number'.

a22PermanentNetworkAddress.name: a22PermanentNetworkAddress
a22PermanentNetworkAddress.description: This is the node address stored permanently in the adapter.

a22CurrentNetworkAddress.name: a22CurrentNetworkAddress
a22CurrentNetworkAddress.description: This is the node address that can be modified by software, sometimes referred to as the Locally Administered Address (LAA).

a22ConnectorType.name: a22ConnectorType
a22ConnectorType.description: This is the type of connector currently being used to physically attach this port to the LAN.

a22DataRate.name: a22DataRate
a22DataRate.description: This is the rate at which data is transferred over the LAN in Mbps.

tNetworkAdapterHardwareGroup.name: tNetworkAdapterHardwareGroup
tNetworkAdapterHardwareGroup.description: Contains objects related to the network adapter hardware.

a23NetworkTopology.name: a23NetworkTopology
a23NetworkTopology.description: This is the network media access method/topology supported by this adapter.

a23TransmissionCapability.name: a23TransmissionCapability
a23TransmissionCapability.description: The transmission capabilities of the adapter.

a23NetworkAdapterRamSize.name: a23NetworkAdapterRamSize
a23NetworkAdapterRamSize.description: This is the total size of adapter RAM in Kb.

a23BusType.name: a23BusType
a23BusType.description: This is the type of bus used to interface the adapter to the host.

a23BusWidth.name: a23BusWidth
a23BusWidth.description: This is the width (in bits) of the data path used to interface the adapter with the host.

a24EventType.name: a24EventType
a24EventType.description: The type of event that has occurred.

a24IsEventState_based.name: a24IsEventState_based
a24IsEventState_based.description: The value of this attributedetermines whether the Event being reportedis a state-based Event or not. If the valueof this attribute is TRUE then the Event isstate-based. Otherwise the Event is notstate-based.

a24EventStateKey.name: a24EventStateKey
a24EventStateKey.description: A unique, single integer key into the EventState group if this is a state-based Event.If this is not a state-based Event then thisthis attribute's value is not defined.

a24AssociatedGroup.name: a24AssociatedGroup
a24AssociatedGroup.description: The class name of the group that is associatedwith the events defined in this EventGeneration group.

a24EventSystem.name: a24EventSystem
a24EventSystem.description: The major functional aspect of the productcausing the fault.

a24EventSubsystem.name: a24EventSubsystem
a24EventSubsystem.description: The minor functional aspect of the productcausing the fault.

a24IsInstanceDataPresent.name: a24IsInstanceDataPresent
a24IsInstanceDataPresent.description: Indicates whether the second event block containsinstance-specif c data.

a24EventMessage.name: a24EventMessage
a24EventMessage.description: Auxillary information releated to the eventThis text contains the name of the Probe

a25EventType.description: The type of event that has occurred.

a25IsEventState_based.description: The value of this attributedetermines whether the Event being reportedis a state-based Event or not. If the valueof this attribute is TRUE then the Event isstate-based. Otherwise the Event is notstate-based.

a25EventStateKey.name: a25EventStateKey
a25EventStateKey.description: A unique, single integer key into the EventState group if this is a state-based Event.If this is not a state-based Event then thisthis attribute's value is not defined.

a25AssociatedGroup.name: a25AssociatedGroup
a25AssociatedGroup.description: The class name of the group that is associatedwith the events defined in this EventGeneration group.

a25EventSystem.name: a25EventSystem
a25EventSystem.description: The major functional aspect of the productcausing the fault.

a25EventSubsystem.name: a25EventSubsystem
a25EventSubsystem.description: The minor functional aspect of the productcausing the fault.

a25IsInstanceDataPresent.name: a25IsInstanceDataPresent
a25IsInstanceDataPresent.description: Indicates whether the second event block containsinstance-specif c data.

a25EventMessage.description: Auxillary information releated to the eventThis text contains the name of the Probe

a26EventType.description: The type of event that has occurred.

a26IsEventState_based.description: The value of this attributedetermines whether the Event being reportedis a state-based Event or not. If the valueof this attribute is TRUE then the Event isstate-based. Otherwise the Event is notstate-based.
